Description: SERVEMERGE merges the core of an individuals personality with the volunteer needs of the community.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: SERVEMERGE® merges the core of an individuals personality with the volunteer needs of the community. Volunteering is a beautiful thing. It’s a way to help improve the lives of people all around the world while making the whole thing a better place. But knowing where to start isn’t always easy. You have to find an organization, dig through their events, find one that fits your schedule and hope that maybe, just maybe, it might be something you genuinely care about. Sounds familiar, right? Many times these tasks get in the way of the real matter at hand. What am I passionate about? What is my purpose for volunteering? At SERVEMERGE®, we believe community impact is more genuine and lasts longer when those volunteering are passionate and proactive with their time, talent and treasure. We think your full effort should go toward serving the causes you care about most — not being bogged down with tasks of connecting and scheduling. There’s a better, more efficient way to volunteer and we want to help you get started. Our platform makes finding your passions and putting them into easy place. Skopos asks, You answer. Skopos is our way of helping you find the causes you believe in and the ways you’re able to help. It’s the core of your SERVEMERGE® profile and the core of everything we stand for. Volunteering may be a beautiful thing, but volunteering with passion and purpose is an entirely different experience.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Other, Social Impact

Description: VIP Piano Club Inc was legally established 01-28-2013 in Reno, NV as an S-Corp in order to facilitate long term cross State growth.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: VIP Piano Club Inc was legally established 01-28-2013 in Reno, NV as an S-Corp in order to facilitate long term cross State growth that'd be healthy for the business's Tax strategy and expansion plans.  We had signed a rent agreement with the owner of Fun & Fit Gymnastics, who has been enthusiastic about having our presence as a cross promotion opportunity, in addition to the additional income from our rent payments.  Yet the teacher we hired already has her own home studio  offering the same curriculum, and could not accommodate the times that initial student families had available . We realized that our hiring strategy needed to focus on obtaining fresh enthusiastic instructors willing to be licensed and trained. This presented an additional funding challenge. Our chosen curriculum, Simply Music - link provided - is a proven method for unveiling natural musicality, providing group music  instruction for babies through 5 years old and piano for ages 4 through adult. The founder, Neil Moore, originally invented the system after he was asked to teach an 8 year old blind boy how to play.  Note reading is intentionally delayed for about a year, which allows anyone and everyone to experience playing great sounding music on the piano - with right and left hands - on the very 1st lesson.  Although the costs of licensing instructors is high, the long term benefits of offering a consistent and pure curriculum - with proven results on 3 continents, is worth the investment in employees, especially for being able to deliver vetted value to customers.  Even though there is a considerable amount of projected revenue from lessons, we realize there is even more that can be generated through digital and acoustic piano sales.  The founder's 5 1/2 years experience in a retail piano store environment provides unique insight and motivation into this ""non retail store"" strategy of selling.  Selling is online based, through client surveys, and comfortable ""subscription plans"" options.
